$Bug: Construction of empty collection results in internal error$
$Category: GUI$
$State: Closed$
$BugAuthor: mk$
$Tests: test/t041$

DESCRIPTION:

  ?oclEmpty(Collection(Integer)) raises a null pointer exception

  INTERNAL ERROR: An unexpected exception occured. This happened most probably
  due to an error in the program. The program will try to continue, but may
  not be able to recover from the error. Please send a bug report to mr@tzi.org
  with a description of your last input and include the following output:
  Program version: 2.3.1
  Project version: use 2-3-1-release.3 Wed, 02 Aug 2006 17:53:29 +0200 green
  Stack trace: java.lang.NullPointerException
	  at org.tzi.use.parser.SrcPos.<init>(SrcPos.java:42)
	  at org.tzi.use.parser.SemanticException.<init>(SemanticException.java:51)
	  at org.tzi.use.parser.SemanticException.<init>(SemanticException.java:55)
	  at org.tzi.use.parser.ocl.ASTEmptyCollectionLiteral.gen(ASTEmptyCollectionLiteral.java:49)

SOLUTION:

  Added setStartToken() to the corresponding parser rule. Now, the correct error message
  is correctly reported.


